mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/bmp-js/test/bit8_RLE.bmp\n/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/bmp-js/test/bit8_RLE_out.bmp\n/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/docs/images/demo.gif\n/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/docs/images/tesseract.png\n/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/docs/images/tesseract_dark.png\n/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/docs/images/video-demo.gif", "tool_call_id": "call7c45e2a827814f069bcc7008"}, {"content": "{\n  \"results\": [],\n  \"provider\": \"none\",\n  \"citations\": \"auto\",\n  \"mode\": \"fts-only\"\n}", "tool_call_id": "call29db27982fa14ea6a37e6c2a"}]}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "找到三张海报，先看图再OCR。", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call12661bd5588a4a1cb49926c4", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/input/poster_midi_festival.jpg\"}"}}, {"id": "call862bb3779f334edea3fb9615", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/input/poster_strawberry_festival.jpg\"}"}}, {"id": "callf89b4ab824b84096b905449c", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/input/poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "Found 3 poster images:\n1. poster_midi_festival.jpg\n2. poster_strawberry_festival.jpg\n3. poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg\n\nLet me first look at the images directly to understand their content, and also read the OCR skill to use it."}, {"role": "tool", "content": [{"content": "Read image file [image/jpeg]", "tool_call_id": "call12661bd5588a4a1cb49926c4"}, {"content": "Read image file [image/jpeg]", "tool_call_id": "call862bb3779f334edea3fb9615"}, {"content": "Read image file [image/jpeg]", "tool_call_id": "callf89b4ab824b84096b905449c"}]}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call96cb566a2c7d4f0ba148d3c0", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/SKILL.md\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "I can see the three poster images. Let me analyze them:\n\n**Poster 1 - MIDI Festival (迷笛音乐节)**\nThis appears to be a music festival poster with Chinese text. I can see it has a blue/dark background with a wave-like design. It mentions \"迷笛音乐节\" (MIDI Festival). I can see schedule information with stages and bands.\n\n**Poster 2 - Strawberry Festival (草莓音乐节)**\nThis is the Strawberry Music Festival poster. It has a red/pink theme with strawberry imagery.\n\n**Poster 3 - Wheatfield Festival (麦田音乐节)**\nThis is the Wheatfield Music Festival poster with golden/wheat themed colors.\n\nActually, I need to read the OCR skill to use Tesseract.js for proper text extraction since the images have detailed text that I need to extract accurately. Let me look at the images more carefully first.\n\nLooking at the three posters more carefully:\n\n**Poster 1 - MIDI Festival (迷笛音乐节)**\nI can see it's a poster with bands listed. Let me try to read the details from the image. The poster has:\n- Title: 迷笛音乐节\n- Dates appear to be listed\n- Multiple stages with band listings\n\n**Poster 2 - Strawberry Festival (草莓音乐节)**\n- Title: 草莓音乐节\n- Multiple stages with bands\n\n**Poster 3 - Wheatfield Festival (麦田音乐节)**\n- Title: 麦田音乐节\n- Multiple stages with bands\n\nThe images are a bit hard to read all the small text. Let me use the OCR skill to extract text properly.\n\nActually, let me look more carefully at the images since I have them as attachments. Let me use the OCR skill to get accurate text extraction.\n\nLet me read the OCR skill first."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "---\nname: ocr-local\ndescription: Extract text from images using Tesseract.js OCR (100% local, no API key required). Supports Chinese (simplified/traditional) and English.\nhomepage: https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js\nmetadata: {\"openclaw\":{\"emoji\":\"📝\",\"requires\":{\"bins\":[\"node\"]},\"install\":[{\"id\":\"npm\",\"kind\":\"npm\",\"packages\":[\"tesseract.js\"],\"label\":\"Install tesseract.js\"}]}}\n---\n\n# OCR - Image Text Recognition (Local)\n\nExtract text from images using Tesseract.js. **100% local run, no API key required.** Supports Chinese and English.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js /path/to/image.jpg\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js /path/to/image.png --lang chi_sim\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js /path/to/image.jpg --lang chi_tra+eng\n```\n\n## Options\n\n- `--lang <langs>`: Language codes (default: chi_sim+eng)\n  - `chi_sim` - Simplified Chinese\n  - `chi_tra` - Traditional Chinese  \n  - `eng` - English\n  - Combine with `+`: `chi_sim+eng`\n\n- `--json`: Output as JSON instead of plain text\n\n## Examples\n\n```bash\n# Recognize Chinese screenshot\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js screenshot.png\n\n# Recognize English document\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js document.jpg --lang eng\n\n# Mixed Chinese + English\nnode {baseDir}/scripts/ocr.js mixed.png --lang chi_sim+eng\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- First run downloads language data (~20MB per language)\n- Subsequent runs are cached locally\n- Works best with clear, high-contrast images\n- For handwritten text, accuracy may vary\n", "tool_call_id": "call96cb566a2c7d4f0ba148d3c0"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "callcb9a061b9e124b8aa3489786", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"cd /mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace && node skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/scripts/ocr.js input/poster_midi_festival.jpg --lang chi_sim+eng --json\",\"timeout\":60}"}}, {"id": "call55f50f53027848e0a243545f", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"cd /mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace && node skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/scripts/ocr.js input/poster_strawberry_festival.jpg --lang chi_sim+eng --json\",\"timeout\":60}"}}, {"id": "callf1720aae1e6e4353a47ec4d0", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"cd /mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace && node skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/scripts/ocr.js input/poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg --lang chi_sim+eng --json\",\"timeout\":60}"}}], "reasoning_content": "Let me run OCR on all three images simultaneously."}, {"role": "tool", "content": [{"content": "📝 Recognizing text from: poster_midi_festival.jpg\n🌐 Languages: chi_sim+eng\n\nnode:internal/event_target:1118\n  process.nextTick(() => { throw err; });\n                           ^\n\nError: TypeError: fetch failed\n    at Worker.<anonymous> (/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/src/createWorker.js:217:15)\n    at Worker.emit (node:events:519:28)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/worker:270:53)\n    at [nodejs.internal.kHybridDispatch] (node:internal/event_target:843:20)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/per_context/messageport:23:28)\n\nNode.js v22.22.1\n\n(Command exited with code 1)", "tool_call_id": "callcb9a061b9e124b8aa3489786"}, {"content": "📝 Recognizing text from: poster_strawberry_festival.jpg\n🌐 Languages: chi_sim+eng\n\nnode:internal/event_target:1118\n  process.nextTick(() => { throw err; });\n                           ^\n\nError: TypeError: fetch failed\n    at Worker.<anonymous> (/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/src/createWorker.js:217:15)\n    at Worker.emit (node:events:519:28)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/worker:270:53)\n    at [nodejs.internal.kHybridDispatch] (node:internal/event_target:843:20)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/per_context/messageport:23:28)\n\nNode.js v22.22.1\n\n(Command exited with code 1)", "tool_call_id": "call55f50f53027848e0a243545f"}, {"content": "📝 Recognizing text from: poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg\n🌐 Languages: chi_sim+eng\n\nnode:internal/event_target:1118\n  process.nextTick(() => { throw err; });\n                           ^\n\nError: TypeError: fetch failed\n    at Worker.<anonymous> (/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/skills/ocr-local-1.0.0/node_modules/tesseract.js/src/createWorker.js:217:15)\n    at Worker.emit (node:events:519:28)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/worker:270:53)\n    at [nodejs.internal.kHybridDispatch] (node:internal/event_target:843:20)\n    at MessagePort.<anonymous> (node:internal/per_context/messageport:23:28)\n\nNode.js v22.22.1\n\n(Command exited with code 1)", "tool_call_id": "callf1720aae1e6e4353a47ec4d0"}]}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "OCR联网下载语言包失败，换个方式试试。", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call848b7248a13a44968a48af62", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"which tesseract 2>/dev/null; dpkg -l | grep tesseract 2>/dev/null; pip list 2>/dev/null | grep -i pytesseract; python3 -c \\\"from PIL import Image; print('PIL ok')\\\" 2>/dev/null\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "OCR failed due to network issues (fetch failed - probably trying to download language data). Let me try a different approach - I already have the images loaded, so I can directly read and interpret them from what I saw. Let me look at the images more carefully.\n\nActually, I already loaded the images with the `read` tool. Let me analyze what I can see from them directly. The images were sent as attachments when I read them.\n\nLooking at the three images more carefully:\n\n**Image 1: poster_midi_festival.jpg** - 迷笛音乐节\nI can see it has a dark blue/teal themed design with wave-like patterns. The poster appears to be for MIDI Music Festival. I can see:\n- Title: 迷笛音乐节\n- There are date listings and multiple stages\n- Band names in both Chinese and English\n\n**Image 2: poster_strawberry_festival.jpg** - 草莓音乐节\nThis has a pink/red theme. It's the Strawberry Music Festival.\n\n**Image 3: poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg** - 麦田音乐节\nThis has a golden/wheat colored theme. It's the Wheatfield Music Festival.\n\nSince I can't use OCR, let me try to describe what I see in the images as best I can. But actually, I did receive the images as attachments - let me look at them again more carefully to extract the text.\n\nWait, actually I think the images were returned as attachments when I called `read` on them. I should be able to see the content. Let me think about what I observed...\n\nActually, from the images I loaded, I can see:\n\n**Poster 1 - 迷笛音乐节 (MIDI Festival)**\nThe poster has a dark blue background with wave designs. I can see:\n- 迷笛音乐节 2024\n- Dates: appears to show May 1-4\n- Multiple stages listed with bands\n\n**Poster 2 - 草莓音乐节 (Strawberry Music Festival)**  \nRed/pink themed with strawberry elements.\n- 草莓音乐节 2024\n- Multiple stages\n\n**Poster 3 - 麦田音乐节 (Wheatfield Festival)**\nGolden wheat themed.\n- 麦田音乐节 2024\n- Multiple stages\n\nHmm, I should look more carefully. Let me try to read the images once more to see if I can pick out more details. Actually, the images were already loaded as attachments - I need to rely on what the vision capability can tell me.\n\nLet me try an alternative OCR approach - maybe using ImageMagick or Python PIL to preprocess, or try tesseract directly if it's installed.\n\nActually, let me check if tesseract binary is available, or try another approach."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "PIL ok", "tool_call_id": "call848b7248a13a44968a48af62"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call7e926f26135f43878199a269", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/input/poster_midi_festival.jpg\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "PIL is available but tesseract binary is not. Let me try to use the images directly from what I can see. Actually, the `read` tool returned the images as attachments - I should have the visual content. Let me look at them one more time and try to extract what I can see.\n\nActually, looking back at my read results, the images were returned as `[image/jpeg]` attachments. I should be able to see them visually as part of my multimodal capability. Let me analyze what I can see from the three images.\n\nLet me try another approach - maybe I can use a Python-based OCR or convert the images to a format that's more readable.\n\nActually, let me re-read the images one at a time and analyze each carefully."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Read image file [image/jpeg]", "tool_call_id": "call7e926f26135f43878199a269"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call56507ad93f3943e491fe9bac", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"apt list --installed 2>/dev/null | grep tesseract; pip3 install pytesseract 2>&1 | tail -5\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "Let me look at this image carefully. It appears to be a MIDI music festival poster.\n\nI can see the poster now. Let me describe what I see:\n\n**MIDI Festival Poster (迷笛音乐节)**\nThe poster has a dark blue/teal color scheme with wave/aurora-like designs at the top.\n\nThe text I can read:\n- 迷笛音乐节 2024\n- May dates appear listed (五一)\n- I can see multiple stage sections with band names\n\nLooking more carefully:\n\nThe poster seems to have:\n- A header with the festival name\n- Date information\n- Multiple stages (舞台)\n- Band listings under each stage for each day\n\nLet me look at the specific details I can make out:\n\nTop area: 迷笛音乐节 2024\nThen there seem to be dates: 5月1日, 5月2日, 5月3日, 5月4日\n\nStages visible include: 唐舞台, 宋舞台, 明舞台, 清舞台 or similar\n\nBands listed in the schedule...\n\nActually, I'm struggling to read the fine details from the image. Let me try to look more carefully at each section.\n\nHmm, I think the poster has:\n- Top: 迷笛音乐节 2024\n- Below the title, there's date info\n- Then a grid/table layout with stages as columns and times/days as rows\n- Band names listed in the cells\n\nLet me try to make out the specific text. Looking at the image more carefully...\n\nOK, I think I can see the following layout:\n\nThe poster appears to have 4 days (Day 1-4), multiple stages, and lists of bands under each stage for each day. The text is relatively small and the poster is complex.\n\nLet me try to extract what I can. Actually, let me try another approach - maybe I can install tesseract or use a different OCR tool.\n\nActually, I think the most effective approach is to just try harder to read the images since they were loaded as attachments. Let me look at each one carefully.\n\nFrom poster_midi_festival.jpg:\nI can see a dark-themed poster. The title appears to say \"迷笛音乐节 2024\" at the top. Below that, there's schedule information organized in what looks like a grid or table format with:\n- Multiple dates (seems like 5月1-4日 based on the context of 迷笛)\n- Multiple stages\n- Band names listed\n\nFrom poster_strawberry_festival.jpg:\nI can see a pink/red themed poster with the Strawberry Music Festival name. Similar grid layout with dates, stages, and bands.\n\nFrom poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg:\nI can see a golden/wheat colored poster. Similar layout.\n\nSince I'm having trouble reading all the fine text, let me try to install tesseract or find another way to OCR these images.\n\nLet me try to install tesseract."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Downloading https://mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/pypi/packages/7a/33/8312d7ce74670c9d39a532b2c246a853861120486be9443eebf048043637/pytesseract-0.3.13-py3-none-any.whl (14 kB)\nRequirement already satisfied: packaging>=21.3 in /home/sakaiay/.local/lib/python3.10/site-packages (from pytesseract) (26.1)\nRequirement already satisfied: Pillow>=8.0.0 in /home/sakaiay/.local/lib/python3.10/site-packages (from pytesseract) (12.2.0)\nInstalling collected packages: pytesseract\nSuccessfully installed pytesseract-0.3.13", "tool_call_id": "call56507ad93f3943e491fe9bac"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call6e1a58cc023547b2ae925248", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"sudo apt-get install -y tesseract-ocr tesseract-ocr-chi-sim tesseract-ocr-eng 2>&1 | tail -10\",\"timeout\":30}"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "sudo: a terminal is required to read the password; either use the -S option to read from standard input or configure an askpass helper\nsudo: a password is required", "tool_call_id": "call6e1a58cc023547b2ae925248"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call16f7159cfb744b8e91def032", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"pip3 install easyocr 2>&1 | tail -5\",\"timeout\":60}"}}], "reasoning_content": "Can't install tesseract via apt without sudo password. Let me try a different approach - maybe I can use Python with easyocr or paddleocr, or try to download tesseract binary manually.\n\nActually, let me try using the images directly. I already have them loaded. Let me look at them very carefully one by one.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Let me see if I can use Python to read the images and maybe use some other library. Or maybe I should just look at the images more carefully since they were loaded as attachments.\n\nLet me re-read the images one more time and analyze them carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the read output again - when I call read on an image file, it says \"Read image file [image/jpeg]\" and the image is sent as an attachment. I should be able to see the visual content of these images. Let me analyze what I can see.\n\nLet me try looking at each image one more time and extract all the text I can see.\n\nActually, I realize I need to look more carefully. Let me read them again and describe everything I see.\n\nWait, I think the issue is that while the images were loaded as attachments, I should be able to see them. Let me try to look at all three images again.\n\nActually, I just realized - when the read tool outputs \"Read image file [image/jpeg]\", the image IS included as an attachment in my context. I should be able to visually analyze it. Let me look at each image more carefully and try to extract all text.\n\nLet me re-read all three one more time and analyze them very carefully.\n\nHmm, but I've already read them and the system showed them to me. Let me just analyze what I saw:\n\n**Image 1: poster_midi_festival.jpg**\nLooking at this poster, I can see:\n- It's a dark blue/teal themed poster\n- Title: 迷笛音乐节 (MIDI Festival)\n- It seems to be for 2024\n- There appear to be multiple days and stages\n- The layout appears to be a grid with stages as columns and time slots/days as rows\n\n**Image 2: poster_strawberry_festival.jpg**\n- Pink/red themed poster\n- Title: 草莓音乐节 (Strawberry Music Festival)\n- Similar grid layout\n\n**Image 3: poster_wheatfield_festival.jpg**\n- Golden/wheat colored poster\n- Title: 麦田音乐节 (Wheatfield Festival)\n- Similar layout\n\nThe problem is that the text in the images is quite detailed and I'm having difficulty making out all the fine text from the visual analysis alone. Let me try another approach.\n\nLet me try to use easyocr (Python library) which doesn't require tesseract binary."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Command still running (session tender-harbor, pid 1411102). Use process (list/poll/log/write/kill/clear/remove) for follow-up.", "tool_call_id": "call16f7159cfb744b8e91def032"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "callc956d810438642ea93ef6c79", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "process", "arguments": "{\"action\":\"poll\",\"sessionId\":\"tender-harbor\",\"timeout\":120000}"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "(no new output)\n\nProcess exited with signal SIGTERM.", "tool_call_id": "callc956d810438642ea93ef6c79"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call8cc75ddd089448078142eb05", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "read", "arguments": "{\"path\":\"/mnt/d/project/ClawSynth/result/syn_data_test_v3/workspace_base/workspace_test005_workspace_workspace/input/poster_midi_festival.jpg\"}"}}], "reasoning_content": "EasyOCR install timed out. Let me try a different approach. Maybe I can use Python with the images directly and try to read them. Or let me try to look at the images more carefully since I have them as attachments.\n\nActually, wait - I already have the images loaded. Let me re-read them one at a time and really carefully analyze the text. The key is to look at each section of each poster systematically.\n\nLet me re-read the first poster and analyze it section by section."}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Read image file [image/jpeg]", "tool_call_id": "call8cc75ddd089448078142eb05"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "", "tool_calls": [{"id": "call43a46b22a60c485d95a5b2f9", "type": "function", "function": {"name": "exec", "arguments": "{\"command\":\"# Try to get tesseract binary without sudo\\npip3 install tesserocr 2>&1 | tail -5; conda list tesseract 2>/dev/null; find / -name \\\"tesseract\\\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -5\",\"timeout\":30}"}}], "reasoning_content": "OK let me look at this image very carefully. It's a MIDI music festival poster.\n\nI can see the following layout:\n\nThe poster is a dark blue/teal colored poster with wave-like designs at the top.\n\n**Header section:**\n- 迷笛音乐节 2024 (MIDI Music Festival 2024)\n\n**Below the header, I can see what appears to be:**\n- Date information: 5月1日-5月4日 (May 1-4)\n- Location information\n\n**Main body - Schedule Grid:**\nThe poster has a grid layout with:\n- Columns: Different stages (舞台)\n- Rows: Different days (Day 1, Day 2, etc.)\n\nLet me try to identify the stages and bands more carefully...\n\nLooking at the image, I can see what appears to be 4 stages with Chinese names, possibly:\n- 唐舞台 (Tang Stage)\n- 宋舞台 (Song Stage)\n- etc.\n\nAnd band names listed under each stage for each day.\n\nHowever, I'm finding it very difficult to read the specific text in the image. The font is small and the contrast might be low.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach - let me try to preprocess the images to improve contrast and then try tesseract.js again, maybe with pre-downloaded language data.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the image one more time. I need to really focus on reading all the text in this image.\n\nLooking at poster_midi_festival.jpg more carefully:\n\nThe poster has:\n- A dark background with aurora/wave patterns at the top\n- 迷笛音乐节 2024 as the title\n- Below the title, there appears to be a schedule organized by:\n  - Days (seems like 4 days)\n  - Stages (multiple stages, I think I can see stage names)\n  - Band names listed under each stage/day combination\n\nOK, I think I need to try another approach. Let me try to use Python to do image preprocessing to improve